That was easy!

2. In xfce run via Application Menu:
Application Menu > Office > Evolution

i. At Welcome:
Welcome to Evolution.

The next few screens will allow Evolution to connect to your email
accounts, and to import from other applications.

click next

ii. At Restore from Backup
You can restore from a backup file.

This will restore all your personal data, settings mail filters, etc.

<unchecked> Restore form a back file: <blank>

click Next

iii. At Identity

Please enter your name and email address below.  The "optional" fields
below do not need to be filled in, unless you wish to include this
information in email you send.

Required Information
    Full Name: Raymond Marcil
Email Address: rmarcil@gci.com

Option Information:
     Reply-To: rmarcil@gci.com
 Organization: GCI Information Techology

click Next

iv. At Receiving Email
Server Type: IMAP+ ===> Exchange MAPI
Description: For accessing Microsoft Exchange 2007/OpenChange servers
             via MAPI

Configuration
  Server:    exchange.gci.com   <=== default presented
             ===> ex-arr-prd01.gci.com <=== From outlook also fails
Username:    rmarcil            <=== default presented
Domain name: GCI                <=== Added

          x Use secure connection
<unchecked> Kerberos authentication

...
Cannot get authentication to work despite repeated attempts.
